<div class="c550_6">
<div id="v550.6.1"><span class="G80 s">Brethren</span><span class="G1437 s">, if</span><span class="G444 s"> G2532 a man</span><span class="G4301 s"> be overtaken</span><span class="G1722 s"> in</span><span class="G5100 s"> a</span><span class="G3900 s"> fault</span><span class="G5210 s">, ye</span><span class="G3588 s"> which</span><span class="G4152 s"> are spiritual</span><span class="G2675 s">, restore</span><span class="G5108 s"> such an one</span><span class="G1722 s"> in</span><span class="G4151 s"> the spirit</span><span class="G4236 s"> of meekness</span><span class="G4648 s">; considering</span><span class="G4572 s"> thyself</span><span class="G3361 s">, lest</span><span class="G4771 s"> thou</span><span class="G2532 s"> also</span><span class="G3985 s"> be tempted</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (if: or, although)</span></div>
<div id="v550.6.2"><span class="G941 s">Bear ye</span><span class="G240 s"> one another's</span><span class="G922 s"> burdens</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G3779 s"> so</span><span class="G378 s"> fulfil</span><span class="G3551 s"> the law</span><span class="G5547 s"> of Christ</span>.</div>
<div id="v550.6.3"><span class="G1063 s">For</span><span class="G1536 s"> if a man</span><span class="G1380 s"> think himself</span><span class="G1511 s"> to be</span><span class="G5100 s"> something</span><span class="G5607 s">, when he is</span><span class="G3367 s"> nothing</span><span class="G5422 s">, he deceiveth</span><span class="G1438 s"> himself</span>.</div>
<div id="v550.6.4"><span class="G1161 s">But</span><span class="G1381 s"> let</span><span class="G1538 s"> every man</span><span class="G1381 s"> prove</span><span class="G1438 s"> his own</span><span class="G2041 s"> work</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G5119 s"> then</span><span class="G2192 s"> shall he have</span><span class="G2745 s"> rejoicing</span><span class="G1519 s"> in</span><span class="G1438 s"> himself</span><span class="G3441 s"> alone</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G3756 s"> not</span><span class="G1519 s"> in</span><span class="G2087 s"> another</span>.</div>
<div id="v550.6.5"><span class="G1063 s">For</span><span class="G1538 s"> every man</span><span class="G941 s"> shall bear</span><span class="G2398 s"> his own</span><span class="G5413 s"> burden</span>.</div>
<div id="v550.6.6"><span class="G1161 s">Let</span><span class="G2727 s"> him that is taught</span><span class="G3056 s"> in the word</span><span class="G2841 s"> communicate</span><span class="G2727 s"> unto him that teacheth</span><span class="G1722 s"> in</span><span class="G3956 s"> all</span><span class="G18 s"> good things</span>.</div>
<div id="v550.6.7"><span class="G4105 s">Be</span><span class="G3361 s"> not</span><span class="G4105 s"> deceived</span><span class="G2316 s">; God</span><span class="G3456 s"> is</span><span class="G3756 s"> not</span><span class="G3456 s"> mocked</span><span class="G1063 s">: for</span><span class="G3739 s"> whatsoever</span><span class="G444 s"> G1437 a man</span><span class="G4687 s"> soweth</span><span class="G5124 s">, that</span><span class="G2325 s"> shall he</span><span class="G2532 s"> also</span><span class="G2325 s"> reap</span>.</div>
<div id="v550.6.8"><span class="G3754 s">For</span><span class="G4687 s"> he that soweth</span><span class="G1519 s"> to</span><span class="G1438 s"> his</span><span class="G4561 s"> flesh</span><span class="G2325 s"> shall</span><span class="G1537 s"> of</span><span class="G4561 s"> the flesh</span><span class="G2325 s"> reap</span><span class="G5356 s"> corruption</span><span class="G1161 s">; but</span><span class="G4687 s"> he that soweth</span><span class="G1519 s"> to</span><span class="G4151 s"> the Spirit</span><span class="G2325 s"> shall</span><span class="G1537 s"> of</span><span class="G4151 s"> the Spirit</span><span class="G2325 s"> reap</span><span class="G2222 s"> life</span><span class="G166 s"> everlasting</span>.</div>
<div id="v550.6.9"><span class="G1161 s">And</span><span class="G1573 s"> let us</span><span class="G3361 s"> not</span><span class="G1573 s"> be weary</span><span class="G2570 s"> in well</span><span class="G4160 s"> doing</span><span class="G1063 s">: for</span><span class="G2398 s"> in due</span><span class="G2540 s"> season</span><span class="G2325 s"> we shall reap</span><span class="G1590 s">, if we faint</span><span class="G3361 s"> not</span>.</div>
<div id="v550.6.10"><span class="G5613 s">As</span><span class="G2192 s"> we have</span><span class="G686 s"> therefore</span><span class="G2540 s"> G3767 opportunity</span><span class="G2038 s">, let us do</span><span class="G18 s"> good</span><span class="G4314 s"> unto</span><span class="G3956 s"> all</span><span class="G1161 s"> <i>men</i>, especially</span><span class="G4314 s"> G3122 unto</span><span class="G3609 s"> them who are of the household</span><span class="G4102 s"> of faith</span>.</div>
<div id="v550.6.11"><span class="G1492 s">Ye see</span><span class="G4080 s"> how large</span><span class="G1121 s"> a letter</span><span class="G1125 s"> I have written</span><span class="G5213 s"> unto you</span><span class="G1699 s"> with mine own</span><span class="G5495 s"> hand</span>.</div>
<div id="v550.6.12"><span class="G3745 s">As many as</span><span class="G2309 s"> desire</span><span class="G2146 s"> to make a fair shew</span><span class="G1722 s"> in</span><span class="G4561 s"> the flesh</span><span class="G3778 s">, they</span><span class="G315 s"> constrain</span><span class="G5209 s"> you</span><span class="G4059 s"> to be circumcised</span><span class="G3440 s">; only</span><span class="G3363 s"> lest</span><span class="G1377 s"> they should suffer persecution</span><span class="G4716 s"> for the cross</span><span class="G5547 s"> of Christ</span>.</div>
<div id="v550.6.13"><span class="G1063 s">For</span><span class="G3761 s"> neither</span><span class="G846 s"> they themselves</span><span class="G4059 s"> who are circumcised</span><span class="G5442 s"> keep</span><span class="G3551 s"> the law</span><span class="G235 s">; but</span><span class="G2309 s"> desire</span><span class="G4059 s"> to have</span><span class="G5209 s"> you</span><span class="G4059 s"> circumcised</span><span class="G2443 s">, that</span><span class="G2744 s"> they may glory</span><span class="G1722 s"> in</span><span class="G5212 s"> your</span><span class="G4561 s"> flesh</span>.</div>
<div id="v550.6.14"><span class="G1161 s">But</span><span class="G3361 s"> God forbid</span><span class="G1698 s"> G1096 that I</span><span class="G2744 s"> should glory</span><span class="G1508 s">, save</span><span class="G1722 s"> in</span><span class="G4716 s"> the cross</span><span class="G2257 s"> of our</span><span class="G2962 s"> Lord</span><span class="G2424 s"> Jesus</span><span class="G5547 s"> Christ</span><span class="G1223 s">, by</span><span class="G3739 s"> whom</span><span class="G2889 s"> the world</span><span class="G4717 s"> is crucified</span><span class="G1698 s"> unto me</span><span class="G2504 s">, and I</span><span class="G2889 s"> unto the world</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (by whom: or, whereby)</span></div>
<div id="v550.6.15"><span class="G1063 s">For</span><span class="G1722 s"> in</span><span class="G5547 s"> Christ</span><span class="G2424 s"> Jesus</span><span class="G3777 s"> neither</span><span class="G4061 s"> circumcision</span><span class="G2480 s"> availeth</span><span class="G5100 s"> any thing</span><span class="G3777 s">, nor</span><span class="G203 s"> uncircumcision</span><span class="G235 s">, but</span><span class="G2537 s"> a new</span><span class="G2937 s"> creature</span>.</div>
<div id="v550.6.16"><span class="G2532 s">And</span><span class="G3745 s"> as many as</span><span class="G4748 s"> walk</span><span class="G2583 s"> according to</span><span class="G5129 s"> this</span><span class="G2583 s"> rule</span><span class="G1515 s">, peace</span><span class="G1909 s"> <i>be</i> on</span><span class="G846 s"> them</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G1656 s"> mercy</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G1909 s"> upon</span><span class="G2474 s"> the Israel</span><span class="G2316 s"> of God</span>.</div>
<div id="v550.6.17"><span class="G3064 s">From henceforth</span><span class="G3930 s"> let</span><span class="G3367 s"> no man</span><span class="G3930 s"> trouble</span><span class="G2873 s"> me</span><span class="G1063 s"> G3427: for</span><span class="G1473 s"> I</span><span class="G941 s"> bear</span><span class="G1722 s"> in</span><span class="G3450 s"> my</span><span class="G4983 s"> body</span><span class="G4742 s"> the marks</span><span class="G2962 s"> of the Lord</span><span class="G2424 s"> Jesus</span>.</div>
<div id="v550.6.18"><span class="G80 s">Brethren</span><span class="G5485 s">, the grace</span><span class="G2257 s"> of our</span><span class="G2962 s"> Lord</span><span class="G2424 s"> Jesus</span><span class="G5547 s"> Christ</span><span class="G3326 s"> <i>be</i> with</span><span class="G5216 s"> your</span><span class="G4151 s"> spirit</span><span class="G281 s">. Amen</span>.  <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (To <i>the</i> Galatians written from Rome.)</span></div></div>
